ined\", \"primary_dataset_filename\": \"data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1903\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"EXTENSIVE DAMAGE TO PROPERTY.\\nDUNGOG, Monday, 10:30 a.m.\\nHeavy rain commenced late on Saturday night and\\ncontinued to fall in torrents throughout Sunday till\\nlate at night. It was the heaviest and biggest fall\\never experienced in this district. The local weather\\ngauge records over 854 points. The river and creeks\\nare flooded, and overflowed their banks. Farms have\\nbeen inundated, and great damage has been done to\\nall the crops.\\nThe ground had just been ploughed for maize\\nplanting. The heavy rains have completely washed\\nthe top soil away. Several head of cattle have been\\ndrowned, fences have been swept away, and gravel\\noff the roads washed out. A number of culverts\\nhave been damaged.\\nSeveral houses in the town are almost flooded, and\\nthe occupants are preparing to leave.\\nThe mail coach between here and Maitland was\\ndelayed several hours owing to the damage done to\\nthe culverts.\\nThe rain is still falling, and there is no sign of it\\nabating.\\nAt Clarence Town over 9 inches have been re¬\\ncorded. The flood is several feet over the wharf.\\nOnly meagre particulars are obtainable.\\nMORPETH, Monday.\\nThe rainfall here up to 9 o'clock this morning is\\n616 points. The Hunter and Paterson rivers are\\nbankers. Narrowgut and a large portion of Phoenix\\nPark are under water.\\nThe potato crop will be ruined.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 29], [30, 56], [57, 104], [105, 157], [158, 209], [210, 262], [263, 314], [315, 366], [367, 416], [417, 431], [432, 475], [476, 524], [525, 576], [577, 625], [626, 672], [673, 691], [692, 742], [743, 780], [781, 825], [826, 875], [876, 889], [890, 943], [944, 952], [953, 997], [998, 1047], [1048, 1087], [1088, 1104], [1105, 1154], [1155, 1201], [1202, 1251], [1252, 1273], [1274, 1305]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 29], [30, 56], [57, 172], [173, 244], [245, 293], [294, 355], [356, 431], [432, 485], [486, 543], [544, 651], [652, 691], [692, 780], [781, 889], [890, 952], [953, 1005], [1006, 1047], [1048, 1104], [1105, 1166], [1167, 1210], [1211, 1273], [1274, 1305]], \"num_tokens\": 193, \"num_chars\": 1305, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.99}}, \"ocr_hypothesis\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"EXTENSIVE DAMAGE TO PROPERTY.\\nDUNGOG, Monday, RUO a.m.\\nHeavy rain aommiiicud Iltoon btturdav night and\\ncontinued to fall in torrents throughout Sunday till\\nlato at night It waa tbo heaviest and biggest lull\\never experienced in this district Pile Janal weather\\ngauge records over 851 points The river und ciceks\\nare Hooded, and overflowed their banka Tarma have\\nbeen inundated, and great daniugo bas beeu done to\\nall tbo crops\\nthe ground bad just beon ploughed for maire\\nplantmg lho heavy rams have completely washed\\nHID top soil away boveral head of cuttle have been\\ndrowned, fences have boen swept away, and gravel\\n»If tho roads washed out A number of cul velts\\nhuvo been damaged.\\nSbvornl houses in the town are almost Hooded, and\\nthe occupants are preparing to leave\\n'J ho mull com li between hero