.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1904\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"A GOLD-BEARING REEF.\\nDISCOVERED AT EUCHAREENA.\\nMr. J. B. Jaquet, Acting Chief Inspector of\\nMines, has furnished the Under-Secretary of\\nthat department, Mr. Pittman, with a report\\nconcerning the discovery of a payable gold reef\\nupon the property of Mr. J. Dalton, about\\neight miles from Euchareena. According to Mr.\\nJaquet the reef occurs upon the rocky slope of\\na low hill, and the outcrop is marked by a\\npermanent \\\"blow\\\" of white quartz. It must\\nhave frequently attracted attention, but it is\\nonly recently that the prospectors, Messrs.\\nLongmore and Woollard, demonstrated that it\\nwas gold-bearing. \\\"The reef,\\\" observes Mr.\\nJaquet In his report, \\\"would seem to consist of\\nelongated quartz cubes, which run parallel and\\noverlap one another, rather than a solid lode.\\nIn places is includes breaks or intervals of\\ncountry rock, intersected by quartz leaders.\\nGold has been proved to occur for a distance of\\nover 500ft along the outcrop. It would seem to\\nbe mostly confined to the face or the hanging\\nwall, the roof ranging from a few inches to\\n18in. in width. About 60ft south of the shaft\\nthe quartz is studded with particles of gold\\nwhich are visible to the naked eye. A parcel of\\nrich ore may be raised from near the surface at\\nthis point. The shaft has been sunk to a\\ndepth of 50ft with the aid of a grant from the\\nprospecting vote. Nothing further than this\\nhas been done to prove the extent of the pay¬\\nable ore. The ground has been pegged out for\\nnearly a mile on each side of the prospectors'\\nclaim.\\\" Euchareena is on the Great Western\\nrailway line, about 20 miles beyond Orange.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 20], [21, 46], [47, 90], [91, 134], [135, 178], [179, 226], [227, 268], [269, 314], [315, 361], [362, 404], [405, 446], [447, 493], [494, 537], [538, 581], [582, 624], [625, 672], [673, 719], [720, 766], [767, 811], [812, 856], [857, 904], [905, 951], [952, 997], [998, 1041], [1042, 1087], [1088, 1132], [1133, 1180], [1181, 1228], [1229, 1269], [1270, 1316], [1317, 1360], [1361, 1406], [1407, 1451], [1452, 1498], [1499, 1541], [1542, 1585]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 20], [21, 46], [47, 297], [298, 438], [439, 599], [600, 766], [767, 856], [857, 934], [935, 1057], [1058, 1168], [1169, 1240], [1241, 1334], [1335, 1416], [1417, 1506], [1507, 1585]], \"num_tokens\": 246, \"num_chars\": 1585, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.99}}, \"ocr_hypothesis\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"A GOLD-BEARING REEF.\\nDISCOVERED AT EUCHAREENA.\\nMr. J. B. Jaquot, Acting Chief Inspector of\\nMines, has furnishod tho Uuder-Socrotary of\\nthat department, Mr. Plttman, with a report\\nconcerning the dlscovory of a payable gold- i\\nreef upon tho proporty of Mr. J. Dalton, about i\\neight miles from Euchareena. According to Mr. j\\nJaquet tho reef occurs upon tho rocky slopo of i\\na low hill, and tho outcrop ia marked by a '\\npermanont \\\"blow\\\" of white quartz. It must\\nhave frequently attracted attention, but It Is\\nonly recently that tho prospectors, Messrs.\\nLongraoro and Woollard, demonstrated that It\\nwas gold-bearing. \\\"Tho reef,\\\" observes Mr.\\nJaquet In his rep