}}","{\"document_metadata\": {\"document_id\": \"17040000\", \"primary_dataset_name\": \"overproof-combined\", \"primary_dataset_filename\": \"data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1934\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"MISS JOYCE COOPER,\\nchampion English swim¬\\nmer, leaving the water\\nafter winning the\\nN.S.W. championship at\\nthe Domain Baths on\\nSaturday. On Saturday\\nnight Miss Cooper pre¬\\nsented the silver sash\\nand trophy to Mr. Clem\\nMitchell, South Aus¬\\ntralian champion dirt\\ntrack rider, at the\\nSpeedway Royal.\\nCOMING EVENTS.\\nOn January 18, at 3.30 p.m., a num¬\\nber of the wives of the honorary medi¬\\ncal staff of the Renwick Hospital for\\nInfants will meet in the lounge at\\nDavid Jones' for the purpose of taking\\npreliminary steps to form a doctors'\\nwives' auxiliary to work for the hos¬\\npital.\\nOwing to the need for more accom¬\\nmodation, the business girls' lunches\\nheld at Farmer's every Wednesday\\nwill in future be held in the Blaxland\\nGalleries. Next Wednesday, Miss\\nBeatrice Tange, the well-known\\npianist, will, with Mr. and Mrs. Albert\\nCazabon, be the guest of honour.\\nThe Royal Empire S