ples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1936\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"VISIT OF AMERICAN WRITERS.\\nTO THE EDITOR OF THE HERALD.\\nSir,—I wish to support the remarks of Mr.\\nCharles Lloyd Jones in this morning's issue.\\nAs one who has played some little part in\\nadvertising Australia abroad, and in attracting\\ntourists to the country, I cordially approve\\nof the methods of the Australian National\\nTravel Association, and I consider that the\\ngentlemen who control that organisation, and\\nwho give their services to the country volun¬\\ntarily have done work of extraordinary value\\nto Australia. But nothing they have done up\\nto date is of more value than this latest move\\nof securing a visit from some of America's\\nmost noted publicists. No one could estimate\\nthe effect of this visit, and it would be im¬\\npossible to calculate its value in money. It\\nis easy enough to criticise, and there is far\\ntoo much carping criticism here of any effort\\nby public men. But this particular move is\\nbeyond criticism, and I am amazed that any¬\\none could have found fault with it.\\nI am, etc.,\\nPERCY HUNTER.\\nSydney, Jan. 16.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 26], [27, 55], [56, 97], [98, 142], [143, 184], [185, 232], [233