n time\\nafter the ivar ends and police the Con-\\ntinent so that there will not be whole-\\nsale slaughter of Germans,\\\" he said.\\nDr. Macaulay outlined the work\\nof the recent International con-\\nference of Protestant Church leadirs\\nheld At Princeton, New Jersey, U.S.A.\\nGerman. Japanese, and Russian Chris-\\ntians had sttehded the talks.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 16], [17, 23], [24, 26], [27, 57], [58, 93], [94, 129], [130, 165], [166, 194], [195, 232], [233, 267], [268, 303], [304, 332], [333, 364], [365, 403], [404, 437], [438, 477], [478, 517], [518, 554], [555, 585], [586, 618], [619, 655], [656, 693], [694, 730], [731, 760]], \"sentence_offsets\": [[0, 26], [27, 332], [333, 554], [555, 760]], \"num_tokens\": 105, \"num_chars\": 760, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": 0.95, \"cer\": 0.026247, \"wer\": 0.174312, \"nb_char_substitutions\": 14, \"nb_char_deletions\": 4, \"nb_char_insertions\": 2}}, \"ocr_postcorrection_output\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"None\", \"ocr_postcorrection_system\": \"None\", \"num_tokens\": -1, \"num_chars\": -1, \"quality_report\": {\"ocr_quality_score\": -1, \"cer\": -1, \"wer\": -1, \"nb_char_substitutions\": -1, \"nb_char_deletions\": -1, \"nb_char_insertions\": -1}}}","{\"document_metadata\": {\"document_id\": \"17945000\", \"primary_dataset_name\": \"overproof-combined\", \"primary_dataset_filename\": \"data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt\", \"primary_dataset_version\": \"v1.0\", \"primary_dataset_license\": \"Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.\", \"primary_dataset_url\": \"https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation\", \"benchmark_dataset_name\": \"hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof\", \"benchmark_dataset_doi\": \"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299\", \"benchmark_dataset_split\": \"all\", \"document_type\": \"newspaper\", \"date\": \"1945\", \"language\": \"en\", \"publication_title\": \"The Sydney Morn aid\", \"transcription_unit_scope\": \"article\", \"segmentation_origin_article\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_lines\": \"primary-dataset - legacy\", \"segmentation_origin_sentences\": \"benchmark - automatic\"}, \"ground_truth\": {\"transcription_unit\": \"W. H. DONALD\\nRESCUED\\nEarlier Report to\\nBluff Enemy\\nOUR WAR CORRESPONDENT,\\nJACK PERCIVAL\\nMANILA, Feb 25.—Among the\\nprisoners rescued at Los Banos\\nconcentration camp was W. H.\\nDonald, an Australian who was\\nconfidential adviser to General¬\\nissimo Chiang Kai-shek, and his\\nsecretary, Miss Ainsie Lee.\\nWhen the prison camp at Santo\\nTomas was captured from the\\nJapanese a story was current that\\nDonald was among the prisoners\\nrescued here. At that time I wrote\\na report stating that Donald had spent\\nabout three years in Santo Tomas\\nworking as a bookbinder. This was\\ntrue, but Donald had transferred to\\nLos Banos a few months before the\\nAmericans reached Manila.\\nThe reason for this story about his\\nimprisonment in Santo Tomas was to\\nmake the Japanese believe that he was\\nout of their clutches.\\nI greeted Donald while he was rid¬\\ning over Laguna de Bay in an\\namphibious tractor. The first ques¬\\ntion he asked was, \\\"Where's Madame\\nChiang?''\\nI told him she was in New York.\\nDonald said he had no plans for the\\nimmediate future except to get out of\\nthe Philippine Islands and recuper¬\\nate from the effects of his imprison¬\\nment.\\nDespite his age he has stood up to\\nthe poor diet splendidly. He expressed\\nthe greatest gratification for the\\nloyalty of his friends who had for so\\nlong concealed his identity from the\\nJapanese.\\nIn addition to the civilian camp at\\nLos Banos there was also a nearby\\nreligious camp in which there were a\\nnumber of Australian priests.\\nTo-day I spoke to Fathers C. Tay¬\\nlor of Newcastle, and J. G. O'Donnell\\nof Tamworth.\", \"line_offsets\": [[0, 12], [13, 20], [21, 38], [39, 50], 