he prospectors, Messrs.\nLongmore and Woollard, demonstrated that it\nwas gold-bearing. \&quot;The reef,\&quot; observes Mr.\nJaquet In his report, \&quot;would seem to consist of\nelongated quartz cubes, which run parallel and\noverlap one another, rather than a solid lode.\nIn places is includes breaks or intervals of\ncountry rock, intersected by quartz leaders.\nGold has been proved to occur for a distance of\nover 500ft along the outcrop. It would seem to\nbe mostly confined to the face or the hanging\nwall, the roof ranging from a few inches to\n18in. in width. About 60ft south of the shaft\nthe quartz is studded with particles of gold\nwhich are visible to the naked eye. A parcel of\nrich ore may be raised from near the surface at\nthis point. The shaft has been sunk to a\ndepth of 50ft with the aid of a grant from the\nprospecting vote. Nothing further than this\nhas been done to prove the extent of the pay¬\nable ore. The ground has been pegged out for\nnearly a mile on each side of the prospectors&#39;\nclaim.\&quot; Euchareena is on the Great Western\nrailway line, about 20 miles beyond Orange.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 20], [21, 46], [47, 90], [91, 134], [135, 178], [179, 226], [227, 268], [269, 314], [315, 361], [362, 404], [405, 446], [447, 493], [494, 537], [538, 581], [582, 624], [625, 672], [673, 719], [720, 766], [767, 811], [812, 856], [857, 904], [905, 951], [952, 997], [998, 1041], [1042, 1087], [1088, 1132], [1133, 1180], [1181, 1228], [1229, 1269], [1270, 1316], [1317, 1360], [1361, 1406], [1407, 1451], [1452, 1498], [1499, 1541], [1542, 1585]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 20], [21, 46], [47, 297], [298, 438], [439, 599], [600, 766], [767, 856], [857, 934], [935, 1057], [1058, 1168], [1169, 1240], [1241, 1334], [1335, 1416], [1417, 1506], [1507, 1585]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 246, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1585, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.99}}, &quot;ocr_hypothesis&quot;: {&quot;transcription