<div id="LC13" class="react-code-text react-code-line-contents-no-virtualization react-file-line html-div ">{&quot;document_metadata&quot;: {&quot;document_id&quot;: &quot;16856000&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;overproof-combined&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_filename&quot;: &quot;data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_version&quot;: &quot;v1.0&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_license&quot;: &quot;Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_url&quot;: &quot;https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_doi&quot;: &quot;https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_split&quot;: &quot;all&quot;, &quot;document_type&quot;: &quot;newspaper&quot;, &quot;date&quot;: &quot;1932&quot;, &quot;language&quot;: &quot;en&quot;, &quot;publication_title&quot;: &quot;The Sydney Morn aid&quot;, &quot;transcription_unit_scope&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_article&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_lines&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_sentences&quot;: &quot;benchmark - automatic&quot;}, &quot;ground_truth&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;FOOTBALL.\nRUGBY UNION.\nPremiership Opening.\nMANLY MEETS RANDWICK.\nAfter several rounds of unofficial trial matches,\nthe Rugby Union teams will commence the dis¬\ntrict club premiership competitions to-morrow after¬\nnoon. Officials of the New South Wales Rugby\nUnion are optimistic regarding the prospects of\nthe season, especially as the New Zealand \&quot;All\nBlacks\&quot; will be here in June, and also as the\nAustralian players have an added incentive to do\nwell in view of the fact that a team will be sent\nto South Africa towards the end of the season.\nEastern Suburbs (premiers) v Northern Suburbs\n(knock-out competition winners) was to have been\nthe main attraction; but trouble In securing suit¬\nable grounds compelled a change in the round,\nand it is likely that most interest will be taken in\nthe meeting of Randwick and Manly at Manly\nOval.\nManly was runner-up in the premiership last\nyear. The team has not been highly impressive\nin the trials; whereas the Randwick men have\nquickly got into their stride, and they hope to\nsweep the home players off their feet. Towers is\nplaying well, and will no doubt cause the defence\na great deal of worry. Manly will be immeasur¬\nably strengthened by the presence of the Waratah\nhalf-back, Sid Malcolm, whose absence from the\ntrials did not allow the team to work up its best\ncombination. The match promises to produce\nexciting football, with the burly Manly forwards\nendeavouring to quieten Randwick&#39;s smart attackers.\nThe premiers, Eastern Suburbs, will meet St.\nGeorge at the Weigall Memorial Ground, Rushcutter\nBay. Eastern Suburbs has a splendid mixture of\nexperienced players and promising youngsters,\namong whom is a centre, J. M. Mowatt, who has\nattracted the attention of discerning critics. Dr.\nA. W. Ross, free from cricket, is again the full¬\nback. St. George Is an unknown quantity, with\nits strength probably in the forwards, led by inter¬\nnational Bruce Judd.\nUNIVERSITY FIT.\nUniversity Is one team which will enter the\nfield to-morrow fit to fight out a hard contest.\nThe team meets Northern Suburbs at University\nOval. University has pleased coach P. A. McCue,\nand the forwards surprised many by the manner\nin which they overcame the tactics of the big\nManly pack In the last of the trial matches. Nor¬\nthern Suburbs has made gains, among them being\n\&quot;Waratah\&quot; Sid King, who, if a head injury has\nsufficiently healed, will play at five eighth. Hem¬\nmingway, University winger who toured New Zea¬\nland as a member of the Australian team last year,\nis another acquisition.\nWestern Suburbs, a greatly altered team with\nseveral promising players recruited form lower¬\ngrade teams, Is to play its first few matches at\nConcord Oval, formerly known as St. Luke&#39;s Oval,\nwhich has been considerably improved. Opposi¬\ntion to morrow will be provided by the strong Drum¬\nmoyne fifteen. Among those making a debut in\nsenior football will be last year&#39;s star St. Joseph&#39;s\nCollege and Great Public Schools&#39; wing three¬\nquarter, J. Kelaher, who is with Drummoyne.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 9], [10, 22], [23, 43], [44, 65], [66, 115], [116, 160], [161, 213], [214, 258], [259, 306], [307, 353], [354, 399], [400, 448], [449, 498], [499, 545], [546, 591], [592, 640], [641, 691], [692, 737], [738, 790], [791, 833], [834, 839], [840, 883], [884, 929], [930, 974], [975, 1022], [1023, 1071], [1072, 1121], [1122, 1168], [1169, 1217], [1218, 1264], [1265, 1314], [1315, 1357], [1358, 1406], [1407, 1458], [1459, 1503], [1504, 1553], [1554, 1600], [1601, 1646], [1647, 1692], [1693, 1743], [1744, 1793], [1794, 1839], [1840, 1892], [1893, 1913], [1914, 1929], [1930, 1973], [1974, 2022], [2023, 2068], [2069, 2116], [2117, 2162], [2163, 2208], [2209, 2258], [2259, 2305], [2306, 2351], [2352, 2403], [2404, 2450], [2451, 2501], [2502, 2525], [2526, 2570], [2571, 2618], [2619, 2667], [2668, 2716], [2717, 2762], [2763, 2814], [2815, 2859], [2860, 2913], [2914, 2959], [2960, 3003]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 9], [10, 22], [23, 43], [44, 65], [66, 219], [220, 545], [546, 839], [840, 889], [890, 1061], [1062, 1144], [1145, 1327], [1328, 1458], [1459, 1558], [1559, 1739], [1740, 1799], [1800, 1913], [1914, 1929], [1930, 2022], [2023, 2074], [2075, 2253], [2254, 2398], [2399, 2525], [2526, 2754], [2755, 2829], [2830, 3003]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 435, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 3003, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.95}}, &quot;ocr_hypot