ps to form a doctors&#39;\nwives&#39; auxiliary to work for the hos¬\npital.\nOwing to the need for more accom¬\nmodation, the business girls&#39; lunches\nheld at Farmer&#39;s every Wednesday\nwill in future be held in the Blaxland\nGalleries. Next Wednesday, Miss\nBeatrice Tange, the well-known\npianist, will, with Mr. and Mrs. Albert\nCazabon, be the guest of honour.\nThe Royal Empire Society (New South Wales\nbranch) will hold a luncheon in honour of Sir\nJohn Sandeman Allen, M. P. , and Lady Sande¬\nman Allen at the Hotel Australia to-morrow\nat 12. 45 p. m.\nThe first garden tea of the Country Women&#39;s\nAssociation branches for this year will be held\nby the metropolitan group council in the\nrotunda at the Macquarie-street entrance to\nthe Botanic Gardens on January 18, at 2.30\np.m.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 18], [19, 41], [42, 64], [65, 82], [83, 105], [106, 125], [126, 147], [148, 170], [171, 193], [194, 216], [217, 237], [238, 259], [260, 279], [280, 295], [296, 310], [311, 346], [347, 385], [386, 423], [424, 458], [459, 497], [498, 534], [535, 572], [573, 579], [580, 613], [614, 651], [652, 684], [685, 723], [724, 755], [756, 786], [787, 826], [827, 859], [860, 901], [902, 947], [948, 992], [993, 1035], [1036, 1051], [1052, 1095], [1096, 1143], [1144, 1184], [1185, 1228], [1229, 1271], [334, 338]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 135], [136, 295], [296, 310], [311, 579], [580, 734], [735, 859], [860, 1042], [1043, 1051], [1052, 1276]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 181, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1276, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.92}}, &quot;ocr_hypothesis&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;MISS JOYCE COOPER,\nchampion English swim-\nmer, leaving the water\nafter winning the\nN.S.W. championship at\nthe Domain Baths on\nSaturday. On Saturday\nnight Miss Cooper&#39; pre-\nsented the silver sash\nand trophy to Mr. Clem\nMitchell, South Aus-\ntralian champion dirt\ntrack rider, at the\nSpeedway Royal.\nCO