hing they have done up\nto date is of more value than this latest move\nof securing a visit from some of America&#39;s\nmost noted publicists. No one could estimate\nthe effect of this visit, and it would be im¬\npossible to calculate its value in money. It\nis easy enough to criticise, and there is far\ntoo much carping criticism here of any effort\nby public men. But this particular move is\nbeyond criticism, and I am amazed that any¬\none could have found fault with it.\nI am, etc.,\nPERCY HUNTER.\nSydney, Jan. 16.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 26], [27, 55], [56, 97], [98, 142], [143, 184], [185, 232], [233, 277], [278, 319], [320, 363], [364, 408], [409, 454], [455, 499], [500, 543], [544, 590], [591, 633], [634, 678], [679, 724], [725, 769], [770, 815], [816, 861], [862, 904], [905, 948], [949, 984], [985, 996], [997, 1010], [1011, 1027]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 26], [27, 55], [56, 142], [143, 513], [514, 656], [657, 766], [767, 876], [877, 984], [985, 1027]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 156, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1027, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.97}}, &quot;ocr_hypothesis&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;VISIT OF AMERICAN WRITERS.\nI TO THE EDITOR OF THE HERALD.\nSir,-I wish to support the lemarks of Mi\nCharles Lloyd Jones in this morning&#39;s issue\nAs one who Ins played some little pait in\nadvertising Austiaha abioad, and in attracting\ntourists to the country I coidially approve\not the methods of the Australian National\n&#39;liavel As-ociation, and I consider that the\ngentlemen who control that oiganisation, and\nwho give theil cervices to the country volun-\ntarily have done work of extraordlnaiv value\nto Austialia But nothing they have done up\nto date is of mole value than this latest move\nof seeming a Usit from some of America&#39;s\nmost noted publicists No one could estimate\nthe efiect of this visit and it would be im-\npossible to calculate its value in monev It\nis easy enoug