to Tomas\nworking as a bookbinder. This was\ntrue, but Donald had transferred to\nLos Banos a few months before the\nAmericans reached Manila.\nThe reason for this story about his\nimprisonment in Santo Tomas was to\nmake the Japanese believe that he was\nout of their clutches.\nI greeted Donald while he was rid¬\ning over Laguna de Bay in an\namphibious tractor. The first ques¬\ntion he asked was, \&quot;Where&#39;s Madame\nChiang?&#39;&#39;\nI told him she was in New York.\nDonald said he had no plans for the\nimmediate future except to get out of\nthe Philippine Islands and recuper¬\nate from the effects of his imprison¬\nment.\nDespite his age he has stood up to\nthe poor diet splendidly. He expressed\nthe greatest gratification for the\nloyalty of his friends who had for so\nlong concealed his identity from the\nJapanese.\nIn addition to the civilian camp at\nLos Banos there was also a nearby\nreligious camp in which there were a\nnumber of Australian priests.\nTo-day I spoke to Fathers C. Tay¬\nlor of Newcastle, and J. G. O&#39;Donnell\nof Tamworth.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 12], [13, 20], [21, 38], [39, 50], [51, 73], [74, 87], [88, 113], [114, 144], [145, 173], [174, 203], [204, 236], [237, 268], [269, 296], [297, 326], [327, 354], [355, 388], [389, 419], [420, 454], [455, 493], [494, 526], [527, 560], [561, 596], [597, 630], [631, 656], [657, 692], [693, 727], [728, 765], [766, 788], [789, 823], [824, 852], [853, 888], [889, 923], [924, 933], [934, 965], [966, 1001], [1002, 1039], [1040, 1075], [1076, 1113], [1114, 1119], [1120, 1154], [1155, 1193], [1194, 1228], [1229, 1266], [1267, 1303], [1304, 1313], [1314, 1349], [1350, 1383], [1384, 1420], [1421, 1450], [1451, 1484], [1485, 1522], [1523, 1535]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 296], [297, 433], [434, 551], [552, 656], [657, 788], [789, 872], [873, 933], [934, 965], [966, 1119], [1120, 1180], [1181, 1313], [1314, 1450], [1451, 1535]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 220, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 1