<div id="LC22" class="react-code-text react-code-line-contents-no-virtualization react-file-line html-div ">{&quot;document_metadata&quot;: {&quot;document_id&quot;: &quot;27582000&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;overproof-combined&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_filename&quot;: &quot;data/03_curated/overproof/dataset2/rawTextAndHumanCorrectionAndOverproofCorrectionTriples/allArticles.corrected.txt&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_version&quot;: &quot;v1.0&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_license&quot;: &quot;Very likely public domain, but not explicitly stated in original source.&quot;, &quot;primary_dataset_url&quot;: &quot;https://overproof.projectcomputing.com/evaluation&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_name&quot;: &quot;hipe-ocrepair-bench-overproof&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_doi&quot;: &quot;https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18824299&quot;, &quot;benchmark_dataset_split&quot;: &quot;all&quot;, &quot;document_type&quot;: &quot;newspaper&quot;, &quot;date&quot;: &quot;1950&quot;, &quot;language&quot;: &quot;en&quot;, &quot;publication_title&quot;: &quot;The Sydney Morn aid&quot;, &quot;transcription_unit_scope&quot;: &quot;article&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_article&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_lines&quot;: &quot;primary-dataset - legacy&quot;, &quot;segmentation_origin_sentences&quot;: &quot;benchmark - automatic&quot;}, &quot;ground_truth&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;\&quot;EQUALISING MISERY\&quot;\nMr. Churchill said that a\nParliament resolved to set the\nnation free would soon enable\nBritain to earn its own living\nin the world.\nOn the other hand, he said, the\nSocialist policy of equalising\nmisery and organising scarcity,\ninstead of allowing diligence\nself-reliance, and ingenuity to\nproduce abundance, had only to\nbe prolonged to be fatal to\nBritain.\n\&quot;The process of establishing the\nSocialist State has only begun,\&quot;\nMr. Churchill warned.\nHe said that the Socialist Gov¬\nernment spent in its term of office\nmore than £17,000 million ster¬\nling, including enormous sums\ngiven or loaned from abroad.\nThey had exacted the heaviest\ntaxation in the world. It was now\n£500 million, more even than in\nthe height of the war.\nThe value of the British pound\nhad fallen since the war by not\nless than 44d.\n\&quot;This has struck a heavy blow\nat social services. Socialist claims\nabout safeguarding or extending\nsocial services are vitiated by the\nfraud of giving only 16/4 and\ncalling it £1.\n\&quot;This is one of the gravest\nevils which we have to face ¬\nand remember, we still have the\nconsequences of devaluation\ncoming upon us to make it\nworse.\&quot;\n\&quot;TERRIBLE AWAKENING\&quot;\nMr. Churchill warned Britons\nthat, if they shrugged their\nshoulders at the perils of the\nfuture, a terrible awakening lay\nnot so far ahead.\n\&quot;Class quarrels and endless\nparty strife on the background of\napathy, indifference, and be¬\nwilderment will lead us all to\nruin,\&quot; he said.\nMr. Churchill said that, once\nthe basic standard of life and\nlabour was secured, the Con¬\nservatives would provide free\nopportunities to rise.\n\&quot;Everyone will be allowed to\nmake the best of himself,\&quot; he\nsaid.\n\&quot;There still remain forces in\nour island that can bring all our\ntrue glories back, and lift our\npeople once again to the van¬\nguard of Christian civilisation,\&quot;\nsaid Mr. Churchill.\n\&quot;Only a new surge of impulse\ncan win us back the glorious\nascendency which we gained in\nthe struggle for right and free¬\ndom.\n\&quot;Let us make a supreme effort\nto surmount our dangers.\&quot;\nMANIFESTO THIS WEEK\nReuters Political Correspon¬\ndent says that the Conservative\nParty&#39;s election manifesto, to be\nissued on Wednesday, will dis¬\nclose the party&#39;s housing blue¬\nprint for a \&quot;property-owning\ndemocracy.\&quot;\nIt will deal with housing, living\ncosts, the values of sterling and\ntaxation.\nAccording to the \&quot;Sunday\nTimes,\&quot; the manifesto will have\na plan for working people to own\nthe houses they occupy, in con¬\ntrast with the Socialist policy of\nproviding houses for rent built\nby public authorities.&quot;, &quot;line_offsets&quot;: [[0, 19], [20, 45], [46, 76], [77, 106], [107, 137], [138, 151], [152, 183], [184, 214], [215, 246], [247, 276], [277, 308], [309, 339], [340, 367], [368, 376], [377, 409], [410, 442], [443, 464], [465, 496], [497, 532], [533, 564], [565, 594], [595, 623], [624, 653], [654, 687], [688, 719], [720, 742], [743, 773], [774, 805], [806, 820], [821, 850], [851, 887], [888, 919], [920, 955], [956, 985], [986, 1000], [1001, 1028], [1029, 1058], [1059, 1090], [1091, 1118], [1119, 1144], [1145, 1152], [1153, 1173], [1174, 1202], [1203, 1231], [1232, 1262], [1263, 1295], [1296, 1313], [1314, 1341], [1342, 1375], [1376, 1405], [1406, 1436], [1437, 1452], [1453, 1482], [1483, 1513], [1514, 1542], [1543, 1572], [1573, 1595], [1596, 1624], [1625, 1654], [1447, 1452], [1661, 1690], [1691, 1724], [1725, 1756], [1757, 1786], [1787, 1820], [1821, 1840], [1841, 1869], [1870, 1898], [1899, 1928], [1929, 1961], [1962, 1966], [1967, 1996], [1997, 2022], [2023, 2042], [2043, 2071], [2072, 2103], [2104, 2137], [2138, 2168], [2169, 2200], [2201, 2229], [2230, 2241], [2242, 2275], [2276, 2309], [2310, 2319], [2320, 2344], [2345, 2376], [2377, 2409], [2410, 2441], [2442, 2476], [2477, 2508], [2509, 2531]], &quot;sentence_offsets&quot;: [[0, 23], [24, 151], [152, 376], [377, 464], [465, 623], [624, 676], [677, 742], [743, 820], [821, 870], [871, 1000], [1001, 1152], [1153, 1173], [1174, 1313], [1314, 1452], [1453, 1840], [1841, 1966], [1967, 2022], [2023, 2241], [2242, 2319], [2320, 2531]], &quot;num_tokens&quot;: 338, &quot;num_chars&quot;: 2531, &quot;quality_report&quot;: {&quot;ocr_quality_score&quot;: 0.95}}, &quot;ocr_hypothesis&quot;: {&quot;transcription_unit&quot;: &quot;\&quot;EQUALISING MISERY\&quot; &#39;\nMr. Churchill said tha